{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/claude-code-settings.json",
  "permissions": {
    "allow": [
      "Bash(git diff:*)",
      "Bash(git log:*)",
      "Bash(git show:*)",
      "Bash(git status:*)",
      "Bash(git ls-files:*)",
      "Bash(git blame:*)",
      "Bash(git branch:*)",
      "Bash(git rev-parse:*)",
      "Bash(git rev-list:*)",
      "Bash(git reflog:*)",
      "Bash(git add:*)",
      "Bash(git rm:*)",
      "Bash(git restore --staged:*)",
      "Bash(git tag:*)",
      "Bash(git help:*)",
      "Bash(rg:*)",
      "Bash(grep:*)",
      "Bash(ls:*)",
      "Bash(wc:*)",
      "Bash(find:*)",
      "Bash(head:*)",
      "Bash(tail:*)",
      "Bash(cat:*)",
      "Bash(sort:*)",
      "Bash(uniq:*)",
      "Bash(diff:*)",
      "Bash(stat:*)",
      "Bash(cut:*)",
      "Bash(awk:*)",
      "Bash(sed -n:*)",
      "Bash(xargs:*)",
      "Bash(tr:*)",
      "Bash(echo:*)",
      "Bash(test:*)",
      "Bash(pwd)",
      "Bash(date:*)",
      "Bash(which:*)",
      "Bash(timeout:*)",
      "Bash(jq:*)",
      "Bash(curl:*)",
      "Bash(mkdir -p plans)",
      "Bash(mkdir -p plans/:*)",
      "Bash(mkdir -p research)",
      "Bash(mkdir -p research/:*)",
      "Bash(mkdir -p docs/notes)",
      "Bash(mkdir -p docs/notes/:*)",
      "Bash(mkdir -p src/:*)",
      "Bash(mkdir -p tests/:*)",
      "Bash(mkdir -p docs/:*)",
      "Bash(mkdir -p /tmp/:*)",
      "Bash(rm /tmp/:*)",
      "Bash(rm -r /tmp/:*)",
      "Bash(rm -rf /tmp/:*)",
      "Bash(touch /tmp/:*)",
      "Bash(tee /tmp/:*)",
      "Bash(cp /tmp/:*)",
      "Bash(mv /tmp/:*)",
      "Bash(docker:*)",
      "Bash(sleep:*)",
      "Bash(pytest:*)",
      "Bash(python -m pytest:*)",
      "Bash(ruff check:*)",
      "Bash(ruff format:*)",
      "Bash(mypy:*)",
      "Bash(uvicorn:*)",
      "Bash(pip install:*)",
      "Bash(pip list:*)",
      "Bash(alembic:*)",
      "Bash(python -c:*)"
    ],
    "ask": [
      "Bash(git commit:*)",
      "Bash(git merge:*)",
      "Bash(sed -i:*)"
    ],
    "deny": [
      "Bash(git push:*)",
      "Bash(git reset --hard:*)",
      "Bash(git rebase:*)",
      "Bash(git revert:*)",
      "Bash(git checkout:*)",
      "Bash(git stash:*)",
      "Bash(git clean:*)",
      "Bash(git restore:*)",
      "Bash(git add -A:*)",
      "Bash(git add --all:*)",
      "Bash(git add .)",
      "Bash(rm -rf:*)",
      "Bash(rm -fr:*)",
      "WebFetch",
      "WebSearch",
      "Read(./.env)",
      "Read(./.env.*)",
      "Read(./*.pem)",
      "Read(./*.key)",
      "Read(./id_rsa)",
      "Read(./id_ed25519)",
      "Read(./credentials.json)",
      "Edit(./.env)",
      "Edit(./.env.*)",
      "Edit(.git/**)",
      "Write(./.env)",
      "Write(./.env.*)",
      "Write(.git/**)"
    ]
  },
  "_comment_on_fork_bomb_rule": [
    "The classic fork bomb `:(){:|:&};:` cannot be expressed as a",
    "Claude Code permission rule. The Bash() syntax only supports prefix",
    "matching (`Bash(prefix:*)`) — exact command matching is not available.",
    "A rule `Bash(:(){:|:&};:)` produces an 'Empty parentheses' validation",
    "error and is silently skipped. Removed to avoid the /doctor warning.",
    "Fork bomb risk via Claude Code is negligible in practice."
  ],
  "_comment_on_role_separation": [
    "Claude Code's permission model is project-wide, not per-agent.",
    "The role discipline (planner writes only plans/, researcher writes",
    "only research/, etc.) is enforced by:",
    "  1. Each agent's `tools:` list in .claude/agents/*.md",
    "  2. The agent's prompt body declaring its role",
    "  3. (Optional) PreToolUse hooks in this file's `hooks` block",
    "",
    "For opencode-grade per-agent isolation, see",
    "PORTING-TO-CLAUDE-CODE.md §'Hardening role separation with hooks'",
    "for an example PreToolUse hook that blocks `git commit` for any",
    "agent except develop-conductor."
  ],
  "_comment_on_git_commit": [
    "git commit is in the `ask` list (not `allow`) so the user is",
    "prompted before any commit lands. The develop-conductor's prompt",
    "discipline + this gate together prevent silent commits.",
    "",
    "If you trust the conductor's auto-commit policy and want clean",
    "phase commits without a prompt, move 'Bash(git commit:*)' to",
    "`allow`. The conductor will only fire it on Section-3 PASS",
    "(clean) per .claude/agents/references/auto-commit-policy.md."
  ]
}
